search:java-spring-boot-security:spring.content:
- Use `mvn spring-boot:run` to run your Spring Boot application.
- Update dependencies in `pom.xml` for latest versions:
  ```xml
  <dependency>
      <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
      <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-security</artifactId>
  </dependency>
  <dependency>
      <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
      <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-actuator</artifactId>
  </dependency>
  ```
- Configure auditing in `application.properties`:
  ```properties
  spring.security.auditing.enabled=true
  management.endpoints.web.exposure.include=*
  ```
- Implement an audit listener to capture events:
  ```java
  @Component
  public class AuditListener {
      @EventListener
      public void handleAuthenticationSuccess(AuthenticationEvent event) {
          // Log successful authentication
      }
  }
  ```
- Use `@EnableJpaAuditing` in your main application class.
- Configure a JPA entity for auditing:
  ```java
  @EntityListeners(AuditingEntityListener.class)
  @Entity
  public class User {
      @Id
      @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
      private Long id;

      @CreatedBy
      private String createdBy;

      @CreatedDate
      @Temporal(TemporalType.TIMESTAMP)
      private Date createdDate;

      // getters and setters
  }
  ```
- Use `@PrePersist`, `@PreUpdate`, and `@PreRemove` annotations for custom auditing logic.
